<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Elbow1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Elbow,</orth> subst. the next joint of the arm below the shoulder: <bibl n="shak. ven 44" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.194" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 194</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.81" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 107</bibl>. <cit><quote>my e. itched; I thought there would a scab follow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.106" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 106</bibl></cit>. <emph>at his e.</emph> == near him: <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.150" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 1, 3</bibl>. <emph>out at e.</emph> == having a torn coat, in bad circumstances: <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 61</bibl>. <emph>to rub the e.,</emph> an attitude of exultation: <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.109" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 1, 77</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>